{"/service/ndnp/dlc/batch_dlc_queenofspades_ver01/data/sn83045462/00280608725/1958030501/0361.xml":{"full_text":"President Says Budget\nIsn't Only Recovery Aid\nIncreased Federal spending is not the entire answer in\nfighting economic recession, President Eisenhower insisted at\nhis news conference today.\nThe President's remarks came as Senate Majority Leader\nJohnson threw his weight behind a Democratic proposal to es\ntablish a Public Works Administration with a SSOO-million job\ncreating fund. I\nThe proposal sponsored by\nSenator Gore, Democrat of\nTennessee, was described by\nSenator Johnson as one of the\nkey measures in the Democratic\nanti-recession program.\nMr. Elsenhower urged against\nany attempt to make spending\nof Federal money the most im\nportant factor in the Nation\u2019s\neconomy.\nWould Aid Home Building\nHe said he believed an up\nturn in the economy will be\nmainly the result of millions of\nAmerican c 111 ae n s buying\nthings.\nHe added, however, that the\nGovernment can do many\nthings to help. Among the\nthings that he said should be\ndone, are encouraging home\nbuilding, easing credit and ac\ncelerating public works projects.\nalready approved.\nHe also said the Federal\nGovernment should watch\nevery statistic as to what the\neconomy is doing and then\ntake every action that seems\nreasonable in trying to promote\nrecovery.\nThe President kept open the\npossibility of a tax cut to sti\nmulate business if the expected\neconomic upturn does not de\nvelop soon.\nNotes Tool Industry Gain\nAs an encouraging sign, he\nnoted a Wall Street Journal\nreport of a spurt in the ma\nchine tool Industry during Feb\nruary. He described this in\ndustry as an important index,\nj-because expenditures for ma\nchine tools make more jobs.\nThe President-said it was\nImpossible to decide now\n25 whether a tax cut, if it should\n~X become desirable, should be\ny-\nC -.if. mkM-\nI See it @fodai/in tills! dee i/@fomomie at dfutnu \u00a3aniburyh&!\ny\nSi\nSap <%f