ific tax reduction move, he\nsaid, details of the situation at\nthe time would determine de\ntails of his proposals.\nJohnson for Contingent PWA\nSenator Johnson told re\nporters he is supporting the\nGore proposal, as one of the\nkey measures in a Democratic\nanti-recession program. Un\nder the Gore bill, the Federal\n1 Government would contribute\n\u25a09O per cent of the cost of\nprojects aimed at reducing un\nemployment.\n\"I believe we should have\nsuch an agency in existence to\ndo the planning now for proj\nects that might become neces\nsary later,\" Senator Johnson 1\nsaid. \u201cThis program could be\nheld in reserve until it might\nbe needed.\"\nThe Gore bill would author\nize a wide variety of projects,\nincluding public buildings,\nschools, recreatoin facilities,\nairports and hydroelectric fa\ncilities.\nDoubt Early Upturn\nSenator Johnson made it\nclear he and other Democratic\nleaders do not now subscribe to\nI the hopes expressed by Mr. j\nEisenhower that the decline ini\nemployment can be brought to\na halt this month.\nInstead, the Democrats are\ncontending that only by quick\naction in several areas can an\nupturn in business conditions\nbe achieved by midsummer.\nSenator Johnson has been\ngathering individual reports\nfrom labor, business and agri\ncultural leaders which he said\nare not optimistic about an\nearly recovery.\nTrap Law Toughened\nOSLO.\u2014Under a new Gov\neminent decree. Norwegian\ntrappers will need a permit to\ncatch live polar bears and\nother arctic animals. Pre\nsentation of a certified con\ntract for deliver, of the ani\nmals to a recognized zoo is a\nrequirement for getting a per-!\nmlt. j\nMMMMtMMMMMM^\nm A 9 AhV i 1 M m W a J m\nV W I J M M mm M Wmm9 \u201cJ|\nML Sim m M f at M m mA* Ijb\nsmim\nGet that Firet-Class Feeling at low coach fares!\nmm M W W V m |ma mm m M j *mM\ni M i T M M m M m mJ iM mk\nInternal Revenue |i\nActing to Relax\nRule on Expenses j\nBy thy Associated Frees\nThe Internal Revenue Service\nsaid today it plans an early\nI announcement relaxing require-\nments for reporting 1958 ex- i\npense allowances on tax forms.\nOfficials stressed that the ah-\nnouncement will be in the form j\nof a tentative ruling. This will\ngive citizens a chance to ex- h\npress their, views before it']\nbecomes final. j j\nIn general, the relaxation is 1\nexpected to eliminate the\nnecessity for reports to many\npersons who receive small\namounts for expenses from\ntheir employers and who make\naccountings to their employers.\nBut there is no intention, it\nwas said, to eliminate the re\nporting requirements for per\nsons who receive large sums for\nexpense accounts and make no\ndetailed accounting to their\nemployers. These are the people\nthe Internal Revenue Service is\nmost interested in.\nSamaritans to Meet\nThe Good Samaritan Society\nof Washington wlii meet ail\n8:15 p.m. tomorrow in the\nBlessed Sacrament Auditorium.!\n5841 Chevy Chase parkway\nN.W. Plans, to raise funds to\nbuy farm implements for a\nCatholic .orghanage in Japan\nwill be discussed.\nTHE EVENING STAR, Washington, D. C.\nWBPXtSBAT, MAR CM S. IMS\nmmmmmmmmm\nBRki m uk mbilt wwnuwi um tin\nKOROITOWA STORE\n1138 CONN. ME 1337 WIS. ME\nDlttrict 7-I2SO tm Cm, fUmii-MOQ\nmmmrnmmmmmmtrnmmmmmm or Lot Displaying This Sign\nFRESH, NO-WASTE DELICIOUS, FLAKY\nI Bdtsville Turkeys FILLETS el SOLE I\n,b 59* ,b 59* J\nH Tender Beef Liver 49c Center Cut Pork Chops lb 89c\n1 CRISP, TENDER WESTERN RED M\nFRESH CARROTS RELKIOUS APPLES J\n2 S 25\u2018 2 29\u2018\nFresh Cucumbers 2 25c Juicy White Grapefruit 3*\u00bb 29c\n85 APPLE PIE RIDGE MAGRUDER'S\nAPPLESARCE CURRART JELLY\n2-29* 29\u2019\nSunsweet Prune Juice 35c ASANT 0mat0e522,3,33 c\u201d 3 ,33 c|*\nCHARGE ACCOUNTS INVITED FREE DELIVERY, MIN. $5.00 1\n1 FREE PARKING AT BOTH STORES\nPrice* Effective Both Store* Through Saturday. March Bth\nA-13","height":"28695","width":"18194"}}
